# Implementation Plan - Debug Registration 500 Error

## Goal
The goal is to identify the cause of the 500 Internal Server Error during user registration. Currently, the server swallows the error without logging it.

## Proposed Changes

### Server

#### [MODIFY] [authController.js](file:///d:/project/Fittness%20tracking%20website/server/src/controllers/authController.js)
- Update the [register](file:///d:/project/Fittness%20tracking%20website/server/src/controllers/authController.js#9-22) function to log the error to the console in the `catch` block.
- Update the [login](file:///d:/project/Fittness%20tracking%20website/server/src/controllers/authController.js#23-35) function to log the error as well, for consistency.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1.  After applying the changes, the user (or I) will retry the registration process on the frontend.
2.  I will check the terminal output (via `read_terminal` if possible, or ask the user) to see the actual error message.
3.  Based on the error message, I will determine the next steps (e.g., fixing DB connection, schema issues, etc.).
